################
# Browserslist #
################
# Configuration for Autoprefixer, stylelint and some another tools:
# https://www.npmjs.com/package/browserslist
# Unofficial site:
# http://browserl.ist/
# Supported browsers:
# https://www.npmjs.com/package/browserslist#browsers
# Operators “and”, “not”, “or”:
# https://www.npmjs.com/package/browserslist#query-composition
# [INFO] Debug — run “npx browserslist” to see what browsers selected:
# https://www.npmjs.com/package/browserslist#debug
# [WARNING] Multiline comments doesn't support:
# https://www.npmjs.com/package/browserslist#config-file

# [NOTE] Browserslist required included versions, not only excluded.
# [NOTE] Last 1 version, not last 2;
# because last but one version for some mobile browsers in Can I Use is obsolete;
# examples for Android Browser, Opera Mobile and Blackberry Browser:
# https://i.imgur.com/hokFRl6.png
last 1 version

# [INFO] Doesn't support any browser version:
# https://github.com/browserslist/browserslist/issues/137
# Reasons:
# https://www.lifewire.com/why-do-people-hate-internet-explorer-3485786
# https://www.quora.com/Is-Internet-Explorer-really-as-bad-as-everyone-tries-to-make-out
# [WARNING] “not ie, ie_mob > 0”, “not ie and ie_mob > 0” or “not ie > 0 and ie_mob > 0” doesn't work
# We need duplicates “not {browser} > 0”
not ie > 0
not ie_mob > 0

# [NOTE] Opera Mini “is a joke, circumventing rather than supporting the intentions of web developers”:
# https://www.quora.com/What-is-the-best-browser-for-developers/answer/Mack-Moore-1
# https://caniuse.com/#compare=ios_saf+12.2,op_mini+all,android+67,op_mob+46,and_chr+71,and_ff+64,and_qq+1.2
# [NOTE] For Opera Mini needs “op_mini all”:
# https://github.com/browserslist/browserslist/issues/137#issuecomment-455494613
not op_mini all > 0

# [NOTE] 1. BlackBerry discontinued;
# 2. Usage stats is 0.02% for February, 2019:
# https://caniuse.com/usage-table
# http://bit.ly/2BGZD7k
not bb > 0

# [INFO] Links to UC, QQ and Baidu browsers:
# https://github.com/Fyrd/caniuse/issues/4463#issuecomment-420143525
# [NOTE] Outdated QQ Browser version in Can I use:
# https://github.com/Fyrd/caniuse/issues/4463#issuecomment-468143487
not and_qq > 0
